The paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The method also aims to learn generalizable and transferable latent codes, which is a goal of artificial intelligence research (cs.AI). The paper also involves generating novel hybrid imagery, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM).
